Calendar milestone product direction:
- The app should include a Calendar screen
- This screen should include a Google Calendar connection flow
- After connection, the app can fetch the user's Google calendars
- The user can choose which calendars to expose to the app
- The system must use only those selected calendars for availability sync
- Busy blocks must represent occupied time only from the selected calendars
- Busy blocks must be synced for one month ahead
- Busy blocks and DailyFlow-created events are different concepts and must remain logically separated
- The system should later create and use a separate Google calendar named DailyFlow
- BusyBlocks should be persisted in the BusyBlocks DynamoDB table
- Busy blocks should include source calendar context when needed by product/UI
- If busy blocks are displayed in UI, they should be able to reflect the source calendar color
- Busy blocks should be fetched and available for a rolling one-month window
- BusyBlocks history should remain available after the first sync, so past synced weeks can still be viewed later
- The Calendar screen should support free navigation between weeks, even outside the currently synced window
- If a week has no synced busy blocks, it should still be accessible and simply display no blocks
- The week view busy-block presentation should remain in the original simple block style unless explicitly requested otherwise
- Days without busy blocks should remain empty and should not display a "No busy blocks" placeholder
- The right-side mini calendar should be dynamic, reflect the current real month and day, and support clicking a date to jump to that date's week
- The top date strip should avoid duplicating date information that is already shown elsewhere in the week UI
- The calendar should support dynamic DAY / WEEK / MONTH views while preserving the current project structure
- The visible month label near DAY / WEEK / MONTH should be dynamic
- In WEEK mode, the visible month label should follow the week start date
- Calendar rendering should remain compatible with the existing Hebrew / RTL layout
- For calendar UI work, preserve the existing weekly structure and improve behavior incrementally
- Do not replace the current calendar screen with a new calendar library unless explicitly requested
- Automatic busy-block sync should use a freshness rule
- If the last successful sync was within the last hour, auto-sync should not run again
- If the last successful sync is older than one hour, auto-sync may run in the background
- Manual refresh should remain available as an explicit force-sync action
- Repeated overlapping auto-sync calls should be prevented

Profile/settings product direction:
- The app should include a profile area with a settings entry point
- Clicking the settings gear should open a small settings modal or panel
- The settings UI should include a side menu
- For now, the side menu should include:
  - Profile
  - Preferences
- Profile should be the default selected tab when the settings UI opens
- Preferences can remain a placeholder until explicitly expanded
- The Profile tab should eventually support editing the user's display name
- The Profile tab should eventually support choosing and previewing a profile image
- Profile images should ultimately be stored in Amazon S3
- User profile metadata should be stored in the Users table, while the image file itself should not be stored in DynamoDB
- Profile image upload should be implemented incrementally and should not skip directly to unrelated profile features
- When profile image upload is implemented, prefer minimal and secure architecture aligned with the existing project structure

Important:
