- Do not skip ahead to unrelated milestone work
- Do not implement Meals, Workouts, Stress, Overview, OpenAI, or Apple Watch logic unless explicitly requested
- Do not invent recommendation logic yet
- Do not implement advanced scheduling logic yet unless explicitly requested
- Do not rewrite unrelated parts of the app
- Do not add unnecessary architecture changes
- Keep the implementation aligned with the existing project structure and the current milestone only
- Prefer the correct long-term project direction over temporary shortcuts that create duplicate work later

Implementation guidance:
- Keep the code simple and minimal
- Do not over-engineer
- Use clear and scalable structure
- Prefer readable components and small focused functions
- Do not add unnecessary libraries
- Use English for code, file names, comments, and prompts
- Reuse the existing project structure as much as possible
- Only create or update files that are necessary for the requested task
- If environment variables are needed, clearly list their exact names
- If backend routes are needed, keep them minimal and focused
- If placeholder logic is used, make it light and easy to replace later
- If a change requires AWS updates, state them explicitly and concretely
- If a change requires Google Cloud / Google OAuth updates, state them explicitly and concretely

Working style:
- Before generating code, first explain the plan
- Before generating code, list which files will be created or updated
- Keep changes scoped to the requested step only
- Prefer production-oriented structure, but implement only the smallest correct piece for the requested step
- When something is not implemented yet, use a simple placeholder rather than inventing a full system
- At the end of every response that includes code changes, include a section called:
  AWS CHANGES REQUIRED
- In that section, explain exactly what must be changed in AWS because of the code changes you made
- Do not give generic AWS advice; base it only on your actual code changes
- If no AWS changes are needed, write exactly:
  AWS CHANGES REQUIRED: none
- Also include a section called:
  GOOGLE CHANGES REQUIRED
- In that section, explain exactly what must be changed in Google Cloud / Google OAuth because of the code changes you made
- If no Google changes are needed, write exactly:
  GOOGLE CHANGES REQUIRED: none